    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [2 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[3 tbsp] </span><strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated haddock</strong> and cook for 5-6 min, turning once half way, or until golden, crispy and cooked through – this is your <strong>crispy haddock</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
